caption: I've ordered delivery from here a handful of times and their food is always incredible.  Their veggie platter and their lamb/chicken kabob meals are perfect.  They give you naan with your order, none of this nonsense places have started in the last 5 years of having to pay extra for what really should be included.  The portions are good. The veggie platter is massive and the variety of veggie dishes in it is exceptional. The kabob meal could be a bit bigger, but i wouldn't say it is disappointing at all.  The price is a bit high for a meal. That said, their food is complex and varied and i can't imagine it is cheap to make. My issue, then, is really with the service and delivery fees Grubhub charges. It costs like $10+ just in fees and delivery when ordering from Grubhub. I wish this business did their own delivery service and i'd eat here MUCH more often. I'd rather give them the money than give corporate grubhub the money (and it doesn't even go to the driver......)

Good experience! I arrived in Baltimore in the evening, and ordered dinner online, as the restaurant was a short walk away. I ordered a variety in order to sample Afghan food, which I’d never had before. It was all really good. I loved the pumpkin appetizer, and will attempt to re-create that at home. The samosa were good. I think it might have done well with a dipping sauce, but none came with my meal. The bread was awesome and made for a great compliment to the lamb and chicken. Everything  was flavorful and tasty. The rice was great. I appreciate the variety of spices and flavors, which made the meal complex and diverse. I also got the baklava, and enjoyed the nutty flavor and crisp pastry.  The only negative is that I didn’t get silverware or napkins, so when I returned to my hotel, I had to get creative with how I ate my dinner.

I didn't get a chance to eat here. I was carjacked while sitting out in front reading the menu. The people inside were nice enough to let me inside even though there was a young man with a large caliber weapon sitting in my former car trying to figure out how to make it go. Some customers followed me outside to confront the guy, but we had no weapons between us, so the guy drove away in my car with my stuff. Anyway. Happy to be alive. Thankful to the staff and owners for selling falafel and also for harboring me in my moment of fear and need. Carjack is no fun,  but nothing was damaged that cannot be easily replaced by insurance. BPD has already found my stripped out ride and are in the process of returning what is left.
